MERGE PHASE (merging sorted pairs back up):

Level 1 — merge pairs of single elements:
  merge([34], [25])    → compare 34 vs 25 → [25, 34]
  merge([12], [22])    → compare 12 vs 22 → [12, 22]
  merge([11], [90])    → compare 11 vs 90 → [11, 90]

Level 2 — merge pairs of 2-element arrays:
  merge([64], [25, 34]):
    64 vs 25 → take 25 → [25]
    64 vs 34 → take 34 → [25, 34]
    remaining: [64]    → [25, 34, 64]

  merge([12, 22], [11, 90]):
    12 vs 11 → take 11 → [11]
    12 vs 90 → take 12 → [11, 12]
    22 vs 90 → take 22 → [11, 12, 22]
    remaining: [90]    → [11, 12, 22, 90]

Level 3 — merge the two halves:
  merge([25, 34, 64], [11, 12, 22, 90]):
    25 vs 11 → take 11 → [11]
    25 vs 12 → take 12 → [11, 12]
    25 vs 22 → take 22 → [11, 12, 22]
    25 vs 90 → take 25 → [11, 12, 22, 25]
    34 vs 90 → take 34 → [11, 12, 22, 25, 34]
    64 vs 90 → take 64 → [11, 12, 22, 25, 34, 64]
    remaining: [90]    → [11, 12, 22, 25, 34, 64, 90]

Final sorted array: [11, 12, 22, 25, 34, 64, 90]
```

